A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Prince George’s County – Substance Abuse Early Intervention and
3 Detoxification Services Fund – Establishment
4 PG 407–25
5 FOR the purpose of establishing the Substance Abuse Early Intervention and
6 Detoxification Services Fund to provide treatment and rehabilitation to students
7 expelled from school in Prince George’s County and cover expenses incurred by
8 uninsured or underinsured minors in Prince George’s County for treatment services
9 related to the misuse of alcohol and drugs; requiring the Prince George’s County
10 Health Department to administer the Fund; authorizing the Maryland Department
11 of Health and the Department of Juvenile Services to refer students who have been
12 expelled from school to a local behavioral health authority in Prince George’s County
13 for treatment and rehabilitation related to the misuse of alcohol and drugs; and
14 generally relating to the Substance Abuse Early Intervention and Detoxification
15 Services Fund.
